title: For Sale:  Browning 78 Falling Block Single Shot Rifle (Trade???)
postcontent:
For sale is a nice Browning 78 single shot, high wall, thick wall falling block action rifle in .300 Weatherby Magnum. The rifle has a 26 inch round barrel with a bright sharp bore and has Browning scope bases with special Browning swivels for carrying strap. Metal condition is overall excellent with original factory blue and no rust. Beautifully grained walnut stock and forearm with deluxe checkering, all original and excellent with no cracks. The original finish shows some slight wear marks consistent with a firearm this age. This weapon started out life as a .30-06 and was customized to a .300 Weatherby Magnum in 1980 by the late Al Perry, gunsmith from Roseburg, Or. who was considered the finest gunsmith in Southern Oregon and was customized at his suggestion. I would give an overall rating on the entire rifle at 85-90% condition. I believe this was manufactured in the early 1970s and was made by Miroku, a top tier manufacturer of quality firearms word-wide and is located in Japan. They have manufactured most, if not all firearms for Browning since then. A new butt pad was added in 1990. Over the years I have take lots of game with this rifle and its ready for the next buyer to continue the harvest.

It's comes with (1) 33 round magazine and (1) 17 round magazine. It takes Glock mags. It also comes with a TruGlo red dot and a nice Plano case. This would be a great gun for someone wanting a lightweight pack rifle or truck gun. You'll never have trouble finding mags or ammo. It has an incredibly tame recoil impulse, on par with a .22 LR. Good for younger people or new shooters. It also has ambi ejection, which means you can choose which side it ejects spent casings. A nice feature for lefties. 9mm is so cheap nowadays you can shoot all day.Overall, this gun is in great condition. It has some small blemishes from use as expected from a gun you throw in a pack. It shoots well and I've taken good care of it. I have no reason to sell it, I just hardly use it. I originally bought it for camping, but I got my CHL and ended up using a Glock 10mm AKA the tupperware handcannon. So, my survival rifle now survives in my climate controlled safe. I will only meet in the NWA area. I also require proof that you're not a prohibited person. A valid concealed carry permit or a current military/law enforcement ID will work. Cash only. I will provide more pictures on request and answer additional questions.
